    <abstract>
      <t>&lt;p&gt;This document describes a protocol, named OAKLEY, by which two authenticated parties can agree on secure and secret keying material.  The basic mechanism is the Diffie-Hellman key exchange algorithm.  This memo provides information for the Internet community.&lt;/p&gt;</t>
